  "notes": "Kashmiri (Kāśmīrī), a Dardic language of Jammu & Kashmir. Rich vowel inventory including front rounded and central vowels. Tonal/pitch-accent distinctions reported in some analyses. Three scripts: Sharada (ancient), Nastaliq (modern official), Devanagari (India official). Retroflex, dental, palatal, and velar distinctions maintained.",
